# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Rust / Cargo
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Compiled files and executables
/target/
debug/

# Claude Code project config — ignore the directory contents by default, but
# track the pieces meant to be shared with teammates (settings, hooks).
# Use `.claude/*` (wildcard contents) so the directory itself stays
# traversable for the `!` re-includes below.
#
# Note: `.claude/settings.local.json` is **per-developer** Claude Code
# permission overrides and intentionally NOT re-included. The
# `.claude/*` rule already covers it; pre-2026-05 the file was tracked
# (drifted in 6+ commits with per-developer permission noise), untracked
# via `git rm --cached` in the PR that added this comment. Existing
# developers keep their local copy untouched (untracked); new clones
# won't see a stale settings file.
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/hooks
!.claude/hooks/*

.agents

/%TEMP%/

# Cargo.lock is usually committed for binary crates, but uncomment if needed
# Cargo.lock

# Backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these (debugging information)
*.pdb

# Generated by cargo mutants (mutation testing)
**/mutants.out*/

